				<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading pagetitle page-header">
					The Whole Booke of Psalmes (Ravenscroft, Thomas)				</h1>

<table>
<table>

<tr>

</th>
<td>170+ pieces
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>First Publication
</th>
<td>1621
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Genre Categories<span class="addpagetag mh555"></span>
</th>
<td><span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://imslp.org/index.php?title=Category:Psalms&amp;transclude=Template:Catintro">Psalms</a></span>; <span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://imslp.org/index.php?title=Category:Religious_works&amp;transclude=Template:Catintro">Religious works</a></span>; <span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://imslp.org/index.php?title=Category:Scores_featuring_the_alto_voice&amp;transclude=Template:Catintro">Scores featuring the alto voice</a></span>; </div><div class="we_file_more we_audio_top" id="we_file_more_2" data-block="2">
<p><b> <u>19 more</u>:</b> Why did the Gentiles tumults raise, Psalm 2  O Lord how are my foes increast, Psalm 3  O God that art my righteousness, Psalm 4  Milton: Incline thine ears unto my words, Psalm 5  Kirbye: Lord in thy wrath reprove me not, Psalm 6  Harrison: O Lord my God I put my trust, Psalm 7  O God our Lord how wonderful, Psalm 8  With heart and mouth, Psalm 9  Tomkins: What is the cause, Psalm 10  I trust in God, Psalm 11  Blankes: Help Lord for good and godly men, Psalm 12  Tomkins: How long wilt thou forget me Lord, Psalm 13  Morley: There is no God as foolish men, Psalm 14  O Lord within thy tabernacle, Psalm 15  Lord keep me, for I trust in thee, Psalm 16  O Lord give ear to my just cause, Psalm 17  Cobbold: O God my strength and fortitude, Psalm 18  The heavens and the firmament, Psalm 19  Cranford: In trouble and adversity, Psalm 20
</p>

</div><div class="we_file_more we_audio_top" id="we_file_more_3" data-block="3">
<p><b> <u>19 more</u>:</b> O God my God, wherefor dost thou forsake me, Psalm 22  The Lord is only my support, Psalm 23  Allison: The earth is all the Lords, Psalm 24  Ward: I lift my heart to thee, Psalm 25  Lord be my Judge, Psalm 26  Milton: The Lord is both my health and light, Psalm 27  Thou art O Lord my strength, Psalm 28  Give to the Lord ye potentates, Psalm 29  All laud and praise with heart and voice, Psalm 30  Bennet: O Lord I put my trust in thee, Psalm 31  The man is blest whose wickednesse, Psalm 32  Yee righteous in the Lord reioyce, Psalm 33  I will give laud and honour, Psalm 34  Tomkins: Lord plead my cause against my foes, Psalm 35  The wicked with his works unjust, Psalm 36  Grudge not to see the wicked men, Psalm 37  Morley: Put me not to rebuke O Lord, Psalm 38  Stubbs: I Said I will looke to my wayes, Psalm 39  I Waited long and sought the Lord, Psalm 40
</p>

</div><div class="we_file_more we_audio_top" id="we_file_more_4" data-block="4">
<p><b> <u>21 more</u>:</b> Like as the Hart doth breath and bray, Psalm 42  Judge and revenge my cause O Lord, Psalm 43  Blankes: Our eares haue heard our fathers tell, Psalm 44  My heart doth take in hand, Psalm 45  Morley: The Lord is our defence and aid, Psalm 46  Tomkins: Ye people all with one accord, Psalm 47  Tomkins: Great is the Lord, Psalm 48  All people harken and give ear, Psalm 49  Blankes: The mighty God th'Eternall hat thus spoke, Psalm 50  Peerson: The God of Gods, the Lord, Psalm 50 b  O Lord, consider my distress, Psalm 51  Cranford: Have mercy on me God, Psalm 51 b  Why dost thou tyrant boast abroad, Psalm 52  The foolish man, Psalm 53  God save mee for thy holy name, Psalm 54  Milton: O God give ear, Psalm 55  Harrison: Have mercy Lord on mee, Psalm 56  Take pittie for thy promise sake, Psalm 57  Farmer: Ye Rulers which are put in trust, Psalm 58  Send ayde and save me, Psalm 59  Blankes: O Lord thou didst us cleane forsake, Psalm 60
</p>

</div><div class="we_file_more we_audio_top" id="we_file_more_7" data-block="7">
<p><b> <u>19 more</u>:</b> Milton: O Heare my prayer Lord, Psalm 102  Johnson: My soule give laud unto the Lord, Psalm 103  My soule praise the Lord, Psalm 104  Allison: Give prayses unto God the Lord, Psalm 105  Praise ye the Lord, Psalm 106  Give thanks unto the Lord our God, Psalm 107  O God my heart prepared is, Psalm 108  In speechless silence doe not hold, Psalm 109  The Lord did say unto my Lord, Psalm 110  With heart I doe accord, Psalm 111  Kirbye: The man is blest that God doth feare, Psalm 112  Ye children which doe serve the Lord, Psalm 113  Blankes: When Israel by Gods addresse, Psalm 114  Stubbs: Not unto us Lord, Psalm 115  I Love the Lord, because my voyce, Psalm 116  O All ye nations of the world, Psalm 117  Stubbs: O Give ye thanks unto the Lord, Psalm 118  Farnaby: Blessed are they that perfect are, Psalm 119  In trouble and in thrall, Psalm 120
</p>

</div><div class="we_file_more we_audio_top" id="we_file_more_8" data-block="8">
<p><b> <u>21 more</u>:</b> Farnaby: I did in heart reioyce, Psalm 122  O Lord that heaven dost possesse, Psalm 123  Now Israel may say, Psalm 124  Farnaby: Such as in God the Lord doe trust, Psalm 125  Allison: Those that doe put their confidence, Psalm 125 b  Johnson: When that the Lord againe his Sion had brought forth, Psalm 126  Kirbye: Except the Lord the house doe make, Psalm 127  Blessed art thou that fearest God, Psalm 128  Bennet: Oft they, now Israel may say, Psalm 129  Lord to thee I make my mone, Psalm 130  O Lord I am not puft in minde, Psalm 131  Remember Davids troubles Lord, Psalm 132  O How happy a thing it is, Psalm 133  Peerson: Behold and have regard, Psalm 134  Allison: O praise the Lord, praise him, Psalm 135  Kirbye: Praise ye the Lord, for he is good, Psalm 136  Kirbye: O laud the Lord benigne, Psalm 136 b  When as we sate in Babylon, Psalm 137  Milton: Thee will I prayse with my whole heart, Psalm 138  Allison: O Lord thou hast me tride and knowne, Psalm 139  Lord save me from the evill man, Psalm 140
</p>

<p><b> <u>9 more</u>:</b> Behold now give heed  Attend my people and give ear  Kirbye: Our Father which in heaven art  Kirbye: All my beliefe and confidence  Milton: Come holy spirit the God of might  Give peace in these our dayes  O Lord in thee is all my trust  Stubbs: The Lord be thanked for his gifts  Preserve us Lord

<p><b> <u>96 more</u>:</b> Kirbye: Lord in thy wrath reprove me not (Psalm 6)  Harrison: O Lord my God I put my trust (Psalm 7)  O God our Lord how wonderful (Psalm 8)  With heart and mouth (Psalm 9)  Tomkins: What is the cause (Psalm 10)  I Trust in God (Psalm 11)  Blankes: Help Lord for good and godly men (Psalm 12)  Tomkins: How long wilt thou forget me Lord (Psalm 13)  Morley: There is no God as foolish men (Psalm 14)  O Lord within thy tabernacle (Psalm 15)  Lord keep me, for I trust in thee (Psalm 16)  O Lord give ear to my just cause (Psalm 17)  Cobbold: O God my strength and fortitude (Psalm 18)  The heavens and the firmament (Psalm 19)  Cranford: In trouble and adversity (Psalm 20)  Bennet: O Lord how joyful is the king (Psalm 21)  O God my God, wherefor dost thou forsake me (Psalm 22)  My Shepherd is the Living Lord (Psalm 23)  Allison: The Earth is all the Lords (Psalm 24)  Ward: I Lift My Heart to Thee (Psalm 25)  Lord be My Judge (Psalm 26)  John Milton Sr.: The Lord is Both My Health and Light (Psalm 27)  Thou art O Lord my strength (Psalm 28)  Give to the Lord Ye Potentates (Psalm 29)  All Laud and Praise with Heart and Voice (Psalm 30)  Bennet: O Lord I put My Trust in Thee (Psalm 31)  The Man is Blest Whose Wickednesse (Psalm 32)  Yee Righteous in the Lord Reioyce (Psalm 33)  I Will Give Laud and Honour (Psalm 34)  Tomkins: Lord Plead My Cause against My Foes (Psalm 35)  The Wicked with His Works Unjust (Psalm 36)  Grudge Not to See the Wicked Men (Psalm 37)  Morley: Put Me Not to Rebuke O Lord (Psalm 38)  Stubbs: I Said I Will Looke to My Wayes (Psalm 39)  I Waited Long and Sought the Lord (Psalm 40)  Blankes: The Man is Blest, that Carefull Is (Psalm 41)  Like as the Hart doth Breath and Bray (Psalm 42)  Judge and revenge my cause O Lord (Psalm 43)  Blankes: Our eares haue heard our fathers tell (Psalm 44)  My heart doth take in hand (Psalm 45)  Thomas Morley: The Lord is our defence and aid (Psalm 46)  Tomkins: Ye people all with one accord (Psalm 47)  Tomkins: Great is the Lord (Psalm 48)  All people harken and give ear (Psalm 49)  Blankes: The Mighty God th'Eternall hat thus spoke (Psalm 50)  Peerson: The God of Gods, the Lord (Psalm 50 b)  O Lord, Consider My Distress (Psalm 51)  Cranford: Have Mercy on Me God (Psalm 51 b)  Why dost Thou Tyrant Boast Abroad (Psalm 52)  The Foolish Man (Psalm 53)  God Save Mee for Thy Holy Name (Psalm 54)  John Milton Sr.: O God give ear (Psalm 55)  Harrison: Have mercy Lord on mee (Psalm 56)  Take pittie for thy promise sake (Psalm 57)  Farmer: Ye Rulers which are put in trust (Psalm 58)  Send ayde and save me (Psalm 59)  Blankes: O Lord thou didst us cleane forsake (Psalm 60)  Allison: Regard (O Lord) for I complaine (Psalm 61)  My soule to God shall give good heed (Psalm 62)  O God my God I watch betime (Psalm 63)  O Lord unto my voyce give eare (Psalm 64)  Thy Praise Alone (O Lord) doth Raigne (Psalm 65)  John Milton Sr.: Yee men on earth in God reioyce (Psalm 66)  Have mercy on us Lord (Psalm 67)  Allison: Let God arise (Psalm 68)  Allison: Save me O God (Psalm 69)  Peerson: O God to me take heed (Psalm 70)  My Lord my God in all distresse image (Psalm 71)  Lord give thy judgements to the King (Psalm 72)  How ever it be (Psalm 73)  Why art thou Lord so long from us (Psalm 74)  Stubbs: Unto thee God will we give thanks (Psalm 75)  To all that now in lury dwell (Psalm 76)  Allison: With my voyce to God doe cry (Psalm 77)  Cavendish: Attend my people to my Law (Psalm 78)  O Lord the Gentiles doe inuade (Psalm 79)  Bennet: Thou heard that Israel dost keepe (Psalm 80)  Allison: Be light and glad in God reioyce (Psalm 81)  Allison: Amid the prease with men of might (Psalm 82)  Doe not O God refraine thy tongue (Psalm 83)  How pleasant is thy dwelling place (Psalm 84)  Thou hast been mercifull indeed (Psalm 85)  Lord bow thine eare (Psalm 86)  That Citie shall full well endure (Psalm 87)  Lord God of health (Psalm 88)  Tomkins: To Sing the Mercies of the Lord (Psalm 89)  Thou Lord hast Beene our Sure Defence (Psalm 90)  Hee that within the secret place (Psalm 91)  Stubbs: It is a Thing both Good and Meet (Psalm 92)  The Lord as King Aloft doth Raigne (Psalm 93)  O Lord Thou dost Reuenge All Wrong (Psalm 94)  Come, let us lift up our voyce sound - Venite exultemus (Psalm 95)  Sing Ye with Praise unto the Lord (Psalm 96)  Tomkins: The Lord doth Raigne Whereat the Earth (Psalm 97)  O Sing Yee Now unto the Lord (Psalm 98)  Stubbs: The Lord doth Raigne (Psalm 99)
</p>

</div><div class="we_file_more" id="we_file_more_18" data-block="18">
<p><b> <u>48 more</u>:</b> I mercy will and iudgement sing (Psalm 101)  John Milton Sr.: O Heare my Prayer Lord (Psalm 102)  Johnson: My soule give laud unto the Lord (Psalm 103)  My soule praise the Lord (Psalm 104)  Allison: Give prayses unto God the Lord (Psalm 105)  Praise ye the Lord (Psalm 106)  Give thanks unto the Lord our God (Psalm 107)  O God my heart prepared is (Psalm 108)  In speechless silence doe not hold (Psalm 109)  The Lord did say unto my Lord (Psalm 110)  With heart I doe accord (Psalm 111)  Kirbye: The man is blest that God doth feare (Psalm 112)  Ye Children which doe serve the Lord (Psalm 113)  Blankes: When Israel by Gods addresse (Psalm 114)  Stubbs: Not unto us Lord (Psalm 115)  I Love the Lord, because my voyce (Psalm 116)  O All ye nations of the world Psalm 117)  Stubbs: O Give ye thanks unto the Lord (Psalm 118)  Farnaby: Blessed are they that perfect are (Psalm 119)  In trouble and in thrall (Psalm 120)  Farnaby: I lift mine eyes to Sion hill (Psalm 121)  Farnaby: I did in heart reioyce (Psalm 122)  O Lord that heaven dost possesse (Psalm 123)  Now Israel may say (Psalm 124)  Farnaby: Such as in God the Lord doe trust (Psalm 125)  Allison: Those that doe put their confidence (Psalm 125b)  Johnson: When that the Lord againe his Sion (Psalm&#160;126)  Kirbye: Except the Lord the house doe make (Psalm 127)  Blessed art thou that fearest God (Psalm 128)  Bennet: Oft they, now Israel may say (Psalm 129)  Lord to thee I make my mone (Psalm 130)  O Lord I am not puft in minde (Psalm 131)  Remember Davids troubles Lord (Psalm 132)  O How happy a thing it is (Psalm 133)  Peerson: Behold and have regard (Psalm 134)  Allison: O praise the Lord, praise him (Psalm 135)  Kirbye: Praise ye the Lord, for he is good (Psalm 136)  Kirbye: O laud the Lord benigne (Psalm 136b)  When as we sate in Babylon (Psalm 137)  J. Milton Sr.: Thee will I prayse with my whole heart (Psalm 138)  Allison: O Lord thou hast me tride and knowne (Psalm 139)  Lord save me from the evill man (Psalm 140)  Hooper: O Lord upon thee doe I call (Psalm 141)  Harrison: Before the Lord God with my voyce Psalm 142)  Tomkins: Lord heare my prayer (Psalm 143)  Blest be the Lord (Psalm 144)  Hooper: Thee will I laud my God and King (Psalm 145)  Bennet: My soule praise thou the Lord alwayes (Psalm 146)
</p>

<p><b> <u>8 more</u>:</b> Attend my people and give ear - Audi Israel  Kirbye: Our Father which in heaven art - The Lord' s Prayer  Kirbye: All my beliefe and confidence - The Creed  John Milton Sr.: Come holy spirit the God of might / - A Prayer to the Holy Ghost  Give peace in these our dayes - Da pacem  O Lord in thee is all my trust - The Lamentation  Stubbs: The Lord be thanked for his gifts - A Thanksgiving  Preserve us Lord - A Prayer
</p>

<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="General_Information">General Information</span></h2>
<div class="wi_body" style="width:100%">
<table border="0">

<tr>
<th class="wi_head">Work Title
</th>
<td class="wi_head" style="width:100%">The Whole Booke of Psalmes
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th class="wi_head">Alt<span class="mh555">ernative</span><span class="ms555">.</span> Title
</th>
<td class="wi_head"><i>Title-page transcription</i> <span class="expandline">
<dl><dd>The Whole booke of psalms&#160;: with the hymnes euangelicall, and songs spirituall / composed into 4. parts by sundry authors, to such seuerall tunes, as haue beene, and are vsually sung in England, Scotland, Wales, Germany, Italy, France, and the Nether-lands, neuer as yet before in one volumne published&#160;; also, 1. A briefe abstract of the prayse, efficacie, and vertue of the psalmes, 2. That all clarkes of churches, and the auditory, may know what tune each proper psalme may be sung vnto&#160;; newly corrected and enlarged by Tho. Rauenscroft</span>
</dd></dl>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Composer
</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft, Thomas</a>
</td></tr>
<tr class="udelonly" data-display="table-row">
<th><span class="mh555">I-Catalogue Number</span><span class="ms555">I-Cat. No.</span>
</th>
<td>None <small>[<span class="icatassign">force assignment</span>]</small>
</td></tr>

</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Harrison,_William" title="Category:Harrison, William">Harrison</a>: Before the Lord God with my voyce Psalm 142) 
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Tomkins,_John" title="Category:Tomkins, John">John Tomkins</a>: Lord heare my prayer (Psalm 143)
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: Blest be the Lord (Psalm 144)
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Hooper,_Edmund" title="Category:Hooper, Edmund">Hooper</a>: Thee will I laud my God and King (Psalm 145)
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Bennet,_John" title="Category:Bennet, John">Bennet</a>: My soule praise thou the Lord alwayes (Psalm 146)
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: Praise ye the Lord image (Psalm 147)
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Kirbye,_George" title="Category:Kirbye, George">Kirbye</a>: Give laude unto the Lord (Psalm 148) 
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Stubbs,_Simon" title="Category:Stubbs, Simon">Stubbs</a>: <a href="/wiki/Sing_ye_unto_the_Lord_our_God_(Stubbs,_Simon)" title="Sing ye unto the Lord our God (Stubbs, Simon)" class="mw-redirect">Sing ye unto the Lord our God</a> (Psalm 149)
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: Yeeld unto God the mightie Lord (Psalm 150)
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Tallis,_Thomas" title="Category:Tallis, Thomas">Tallis</a>: <a href="/wiki/Praise_the_Lord_O_Ye_Gentils_All_(Tallis,_Thomas)" title="Praise the Lord O Ye Gentils All (Tallis, Thomas)">Praise the Lord O Ye Gentils all - A Psalme before Morning Prayer</a>
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: Behold now give heed - A Psalme before Evening Prayer 
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: Attend my people and give ear - Audi Israel
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Kirbye,_George" title="Category:Kirbye, George">Kirbye</a>: Our Father which in heaven art - The Lord' s Prayer
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Kirbye,_George" title="Category:Kirbye, George">Kirbye</a>: All my beliefe and confidence - The Creed 
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Milton_Sr.,_John" title="Category:Milton Sr., John">John Milton Sr.</a>: Come holy spirit the God of might - A Prayer to the holy Ghost
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: Give peace in these our dayes - Da pacem
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: O Lord in thee is all my trust - The Lamentation 
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Stubbs,_Simon" title="Category:Stubbs, Simon">Stubbs</a>: The Lord be thanked for his gifts - A Thanksgiving 
</li><li><a href="/wiki/Category:Ravenscroft,_Thomas" title="Category:Ravenscroft, Thomas">Ravenscroft</a>: Preserve us Lord - A Prayer
</li></ul>
</td></tr>
